The paper deals with the first-order theory of the real numbers, which is a topic in mathematical logic and model theory, suggesting cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) as the most likely category. The use of continuous functions and piece-wise interval approximations suggests cs.SC (Symbolic Computation), while the mention of algorithms and satisfiability checking suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of perturbations and the notion of degree suggests cs.MS (Mathematical Software), and the use of approximations suggests cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
